commit.message:
Removed pure_count and added indirection methods to _SinonStubCondition

Fixes note35/sinon#40
Fixes note35/sinon#43

Removed 'target' dirty hack

Fixes note35/sinon#36

Call count is not reset anymore on returns/throws

Fixes note35/sinon#32
Fixes note35/sinon#35

Corrected precedence of onCall, withArgs & returns/throws

Fixes note35/sinon#23
Fixes note35/sinon#29
Fixes note35/sinon#31

Removed _get_original from SinonStub

  * Removed recursion and simplified readability
  * SinonStubCondition now starts with
    underscore ("_") to show that it is package
    private and not for end-user consumption
  * Renamed __copy_of to _copy (less awkward).
    Also, after removing _get_original it was
    no longer possible for __copy_of to remain
    private.

For SinonStub, it's now possible to chain multiple returns calls

- e.g.
stub.withArgs(42).onFirstCall().returns(1).onSecondCall().returns(2)
- Makes progress toward fixing note35/sinon#23

Fixes note35/sinon#30

Fixed off-by-one error in SinonStub.onCall
